00:48:53,073 --> 00:48:54,313
All right, I gotcha.

882
00:48:54,433 --> 00:48:56,434
<i>Baker: Oren, suit pressure, 3.5.</i>

883
00:49:07,954 --> 00:49:09,474
Simon:
Come on, come on.

884
00:49:13,794 --> 00:49:14,914
How's my time?

885
00:49:14,914 --> 00:49:16,194
<i>Tanner: 23:57.</i>

886
00:49:16,274 --> 00:49:19,274
Another 6 minutes, they won't
have time to get back to us.

887
00:49:20,674 --> 00:49:22,393
Blow the tethers.
Let's go get 'em.

888
00:49:22,393 --> 00:49:23,154
If we go after them,

889
00:49:23,234 --> 00:49:24,715
we may not have enough fuel
to get off the surface.

890
00:49:24,835 --> 00:49:26,114
Blow the goddam tethers.

891
00:49:26,195 --> 00:49:27,995
Mole 3 at depth.

892
00:49:28,115 --> 00:49:29,755
We're heading your way, Oren.

893
00:49:30,554 --> 00:49:33,195
Tanner: Calculate exactly how much prop
we need to get off this rock.

894
00:49:33,315 --> 00:49:35,395
We'll shut it down when we hit it.

895
00:49:35,474 --> 00:49:36,594
Will do.

896
00:49:45,274 --> 00:49:47,474
It opens up into a cave down here.

897
00:49:47,554 --> 00:49:49,194
Mole got jammed against the side.

898
00:49:50,754 --> 00:49:52,754
Partenza: OK, Fish, team 2 at location 4.

899
00:49:52,833 --> 00:49:53,914
Give me your hand.

900
00:49:57,195 --> 00:49:58,874
- What the hell happened?
- I don't know.  I don't know.

